The paper studies a strategic model of marketing and product consumption in social networks, which involves decision-making by firms and agents in a network. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

Firstly, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a likely category as the paper focuses on the diffusion of products in social networks. Secondly, cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is also a possible category as the paper involves decision-making by multiple agents (firms and consumers) in a competitive environment. Thirdly, cs.GT (Game Theory) is another possible category as the paper uses game theory to analyze the strategic interactions between firms and consumers. Fourthly, cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possible category as the paper involves optimization and allocation of budgets. Finally, cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) is also a possible category as the paper studies the behavior of agents in a social network.
